<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-148-003 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 787 464</DOCID><JOURNAL>EDGE: Work-Group Computing Report  May 27 1991 v2 n53 p1(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT EDGE Publishing 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Multimedia: Media Vision readies multimedia upgrade kit for286-386-486; includes bundled software and Sony CD ROM drive.andO;(Media Vision Inc.'s offers microcomputer upgrade kit) (productannouncement)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Media Vision Inc. (Product introduction).andO;Product:   Multimedia Upgrade Kit (Multimedia software) (Productintroduction).andO;Topic:     Multimedia SoftwareBundled SoftwareUpgradingProduct IntroductionSoftware packages.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>The industry excitement generated by Microsoft Corp.'s recent announcement ofthe Windows Multimedia environment, has prompted Media Vision Inc. to revealthe specifications and pricing of its Multimedia PC upgrade kit, which willbe available as soon as the Windows Multimedia environment is ready.andM;The Media Vision Multimedia Upgrade Kit, as the name implies, is a completesolution which allows the easy and affordable conversion of any existing 10mHz or faster PC/AT -- 286, 386 or 486 -- into a powerful Multimedia PCsystem.andP;  The simple installation, guided by on-line help, brings users up tothe MPC standard.andM;The kit's software elements include Microsoft Windows 3.0 plus MultimediaWindows Extensions 1.0 and the HyperGuide CD-based on-line user manual forthe Multimedia Windows environment.andP;  The kit introduces users to multimediawith a variety of software demos from leading industry vendors.andP;  To provideimmediate multimedia enrichment, the kit includes two CD applications:  &quot;TheMicrosoft Bookshelf for Windows&quot; and &quot;Jones in the Fast Lane&quot; by SierraOn-Line.andM;All hardware necessary to bring the PC up to MPC standard comes with the kit,with an option for either an internal or external Sony CD ROM drive.andP;  Bothdrives are SCSI devices with an average access time of 380 ms.andP;  The crucialelement of the kit, Media Vision's Pro AudioSpectrum adaptor board, provideshigh quality stereo sound and full MIDI mixing capabilities.andM;Media Vision's Multimedia Upgrade Kit lists a suggested retail price of $995,with the internal Sony CD ROM drive, and $1,295 with the external drive.andM;The Multimedia Upgrade Kit is the second in a line of hardware and softwareproducts from Media Vision.andP;  The company's goal is to enable computer ownersto affordably upgrade their current machines to full multimedia capabilities.andM;Media Vision is in Fremont, Calif.andO;</TEXT></DOC>